[Patient] How much water should I drink daily to manage my heart failure?
[Educator] Aim for 1.5-2 liters per day, but follow your doctor's advice on fluid restriction.
[Patient] What if I feel thirsty all the time?
[Educator] Try sucking on ice chips or rinsing your mouth with water to help with thirst.
[Patient] Can I drink other fluids like juice or soda?
[Educator] Stick to water and limit fluids high in sugar or sodium to manage your heart failure.
[Patient] How do I know if I'm drinking too much fluid?
[Educator] Watch for swelling in your legs, sudden weight gain, or shortness of breath. 
[Patient] What should I do if I notice these symptoms?
[Educator] Contact your doctor immediately and follow their instructions to manage your heart failure.